    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-02-03T03:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-02-03T03:00:00-05:00" n="635"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d635">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.1541/139: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-02-03T15:00:00+07:00"
                            >February 3, 1941—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received February 3—10 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>56. …</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <p>3. General Chiang Kai-shek informed me on January 29th that he had placed Yu
                    Pei-feng, who has had much experience in communications activities, in charge of
                    transport activities on the Burma Road as from February 1, and he expressed the
                    conviction that the amount of traffic along the Burma route, which has been
                    disappointingly little during recent months, would show rapid improvement. I am
                    also reliably informed that T. L. Soong has been relieved of the directorship of
                    the Southwest Transportation Company, having been replaced by an engineer named
                    Ching.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
